50 SECTION 5. Said chapter 143 is hereby amended by adding the following section:-
51 Section 102. (a)(1) In any municipality that accepts this section in the manner provided in
52 section 4 of chapter 4, an apartment or dwelling unit in any structure containing 3 or more
53 dwelling units shall not be occupied for human habitation, after a vacancy, until a certificate of
54 occupancy has been issued by the building inspector, certifying that such apartment or dwelling
55 unit: (i) conforms to the requirements of the applicable housing ordinances of the municipality;
